'''Sundance Glacier''' is located in the [[U.S. state]] of [[Montana]]. The glacier is situated in the [[Beartooth Mountains]] at an elevation of {{convert|10600|ft|m}} above sea level and is immediately northeast of [[Castle Rock Mountain]].<ref name=TopoQuest>{{cite web|url=http://www.topoquest.com/map.php?lat=45.10300&lon=-109.64295&datum=nad83&zoom=4|title=Castle Mountain, MT|publisher=TopoQuest (USGS Quad)|format=Map|accessdate=2010-11-13}}</ref> The glacier covers approximately {{convert|70|acres|km2}} and is located in a deep [[cirque]] below Castle Rock Mountain.
